4 My sisters came to town for a visit and we explored the Scottsdale Fashion Square Mall (which is an adventure in itself) and came across this restaurant.  It was a Friday afternoon around 2 p.m. and there was no wait, which isn't surprising for the off time.  The hostess was extremely nice and we had a fun conversation on the way to the table.    The catfish beignets and trio of dips were great appetizers!  If you can only pick one - go for the catfish!  The flank steak my sister ordered was pretty chewy and our least favorite of the things we ordered.  The flavor was excellent, but the chewy factor killed the idea of it.    The southwest chicken that my other sister ordered was excellent.  Cooked perfectly and still juicy it was most definitely the better of the two meals.    Service was great, the food was good (knocked just a touch for the chewy steak), and the atmosphere was festive.  It's a "must-try" for any visitor or local looking for a good meal.
3 Enjoyed the outside, next to the street that goes from the parking lot to the garage, patio. Entree I ordered had very fatty steak.
4 Wow.  You could knock me over with a feather.  On a day when several other much nicer restaurants refused my reservation for ten, Z'Tejas gladly accepted my group, and gave us a heck of a meal on top of that!  Now, I'm not a real big fan of Z'Tejas.  To me, it's just another chain restaurant selling a corporate concept experience.  In the past, I've had happy hour at the Shea/Tatum location and have been seriously underwhelmed.  About the best I could say about that place is the cornbread is good.  But then it better be good at every one of them.  It was my daughter's twenty-first birthday, and it's tradition in my family that the birthday person picks the restaurant.  My heart sank as she mentioned this place, and I resigned myself to another cookie-cutter meal.  Alas, this would not be so, if Z'Tejas had anything to do with it.  Well, ok, it was cookie-cutter, but it was also good, flavorful, spicy cookie-cutter.  It's refreshing when they are not afraid to add some seasonings.    Dishes enjoyed were the Steak Burrito - nothing to brag about, but the filling was perfectly seasoned, hot but not too hot, the steak was a bit tough and the flour tortilla was under-cooked - it should have spent some time on the griddle on it's trip from bag to plate, a bit of browning would add flavor and texture.  The Chicken Diablo pasta dish looked awesome, garnished with slices of fresh jalepeno and served with a savory alfredo-style sauce.  Street tacos were tasty too, but suffered from the same tough steak strips.  Vegetarian tacos were delish, and spicy too.  The Tejas burger was enjoyed immensely the next day, with my daughter saying she would go back to have another.  We also had the Nachos trio appetizer, chips, salsa, fresh guacamole and a white cheese sauce - the guac and salsa and chips were "all you can eat" making the hefty price tag seem a bit more reasonable.  Service was spot-on, the pace was good, nobody missed anything and special requests were attended to immediately.  All in all it was a good experience, enjoyed by all.
4 OK, go here and get the Chicken Diablo Pasta and thank me later!!!
2 I don't get the love for Z'Tejas.Yes, its better than chains like On the Border, Chevy's, or Olive Garden but its still a chain and really nothing special. The appetizers aren't bad, but nothing on the menu blows my socks off.   The atmosphere is, well what atmosphere? It's just kind of a generic restaurant. Plus the servers seem so artificially peppy that I'm tempted to ask if they are wearing the requisite amount of flair... I know, I know, they don't actually wear flair, but it has that feel.  Plus, I hate it when the manager is clearly tasked with going around to every table and checking on your meal. Do it because you care, not just because its a required part of the job.  Both the waiter and the manager came around numerous times during our meal and the question was always "Is everything great!" I wanted to respond that you both keep walking up at inopportune times and interrupting our conversation, so no its not great now, but I was with coworkers and decided to be his nice.  That being said, with so many other good restaurants nearby, I see no reason to go back to Z'Tejas anytime soon.
